Table 2 Theoretical modelling (selected publications)
Pore Approach Comments Ref.
aHL Molecular dynamics Developing tools to perform molecular dynamics modelling of translocation of single DNA molecules through the aHL pore; modelling the blockage current as a function of the DNA orientation
170, 284–288
SiN Molecular dynamics Molecular dynamics of DNA translocation through silicon nitride nanopores; discussion of the relationship between the blockage current and the DNA sequence; studying the voltage threshold for the translocation through a synthetic pore dsDNA that is bound to a restriction enzyme
196–198, 289, 290
Single-nanopore metaloxide-semiconductor (MOS) capacitor
Molecular dynamics DNA translocation through the nanopore capacitor was simulated by the molecular dynamics methods, while the voltage response of the system was modelled by a 3D self-consistent Poisson solver. Voltage changes in the 1 nm nanopore capacitor were predicted to be sufficiently sensitive to resolve single DNA bases
291–293
Gold, carbon nanotubes and copper electrodes
Calculating transverse conductance through DNA
Transverse transport through DNA is studied when the molecule is placed between two Au electrodes. The transverse currents through the four DNA bases were found to be sufficiently different so that their measurements could become the basis for DNA sequencing. Studies with the gap between two carbon nanotubes and copper electrodes were performed as well
10, 294–299
Model nanoporous systems
Developing model systems for studying translocation of molecules and particles through single nanopores
Modelling based on Langevin dynamics, Monte Carlo, and molecular dynamics aimed at understanding fundamental physical phenomena that underlie translocation of a polymer through a nanopore
